---
description: Backend rules for Spring Boot ecommerce system
alwaysApply: false
---

## Tech Stack
- Java 21
- Spring Boot
- Spring Data JPA
- MySQL
- Spring Security (JWT)

## Architecture
- Controller → Service → Repository
- Use DTO pattern (never expose entities)
- Use ServiceImpl for business logic

## Entities
- User
- Product
- Category
- Cart
- CartItem
- Order
- OrderItem
- Review
- Wishlist

## Backend Rules
- Use @Entity for models
- Use @RestController for APIs
- Use @Service for business logic
- Use @Repository for data access
- Use Lombok to reduce boilerplate

## API Design
- Use RESTful endpoints (/api/products)
- Return ResponseEntity
- Use proper HTTP status codes

## Validation
- Use @Valid in controllers
- Use annotations:
  - @NotBlank
  - @Positive
  - @Email

## Security
- Use JWT authentication
- Encrypt passwords using BCrypt
- Protect endpoints based on roles

## Performance
- Use pagination (Pageable)
- Avoid N+1 queries
- Optimize queries when needed

## Error Handling
- Use @RestControllerAdvice
- Return structured JSON errors
